# Pchelovod

> {{ site.name }} — {{ site.description }}

Pchelovod is a family-run apiary and beehive producer based in Tajikistan, operating at 2,400–3,600 m altitude in the mountains of Tajikistan. The site is a multilingual marketing presence (EN / RU / TG). There is no e-commerce or shopping cart.

## Key facts

- Family apiary at 2,400–3,600 m in the mountains of Tajikistan
- Three honey varieties: Mountain Wildflower (multi-floral alpine, 2,500 m), Acacia (pale gold, slow to crystallize), High-Altitude Meadow (above 3,000 m, limited annual harvest)
- Honey is raw, unfiltered, small-batch — not mass-produced
- Handmade wooden beehives from local Tajik timber, three generations of tradition
- Beehives available to other apiaries on request
- Carnica Sklenar queen bees bred and sold — adapted to mountain climates, available by order spring and summer
- Based in Dushanbe, Tajikistan (country code: TJ)
- Contact: {{ site.contactEmail }} | Telegram: t.me/pchelovod | WhatsApp available

